    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "Unitary operators on the two-dimensional vector space \\[ScriptCapitalV] \
associated with a single qubit form the unitary group U (2). In the standard \
logical basis, they are represented by 2 * 2 unitary matrices. We first take \
a look at some special examples and discuss the general properties of the \
single-qubit unitary operations. See also Section 2.1 of the Quantum Workbook \
(2022). The Pauli gate operations (or Pauli gates for short) are defined by \
the corresponding Pauli matrices", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
